claims:
Claims Claims 1. A well pumping assembly, comprising: a housing (33) having a longitudinal axis (19); a stator (37) mounted in the housing, the stator having an axially extending stator cavity (39), the stator having windings (127) that when powered create an electromagnetic field into the stator cavity; a pump (41) having a landed position within the stator cavity, the pump having a non rotating pump portion (43) and a rotating pump portion (45); magnets (47) mounted on the rotating pump portion that impart rotation to the rotating pump portion in response to the electromagnetic field; and characterized by: a neck (49) on a downstream end of the pump having a running and retrieval feature (51) for engagement by a running and retrieving tool to retrieve the pump from and install the pump in the landed position. 2. The assembly according to claim 1, wherein the pump comprises a centrifugal pump (41). 3. The assembly according to claim 1, wherein the pump comprises a progressing cavity pump (67). 4, The assembly according to claim 1, wherein; the stator will accept the pump when the pump is a centrifugal pump and also when the pump is a progressing cavity pump. 5. The assembly according to claim 1, further comprising: a support member (59) mounted in an upstream end of the housing, the support member having a receptacle (60); an anchor (57) secured to and protruding from an upstream end of the pump that is received within the receptacle when the pump is in the landed position; and mating torque surfaces (61) between the anchor and the receptacle, preventing rotation of the anchor relative to the receptacle. 6 The assembly according to claim 1, further comprising: a head (15) secured to the downstream end of the housing, the head having a bore (21) in axial alignment with the stator cavity; wherein the neck extends sealingly through the bore while the pump is in the landed position; and 

 the running and retrieval feature is downstream of the bore while the pump is in the landed position. 7. The assembly according to claim 1, wherein: the non-rotating portion of the pump comprises a plurality of diffusers (43); the rotating portion of the pump comprises an impeller (45) rotatably mounted between each of the diffusers; each of the magnets is mounted to one of the impellers; and the impellers are rotationally located to each other for rotation in unison. 8. The assembly according to claim 1, wherein: the rotating portion of the pump comprises a tube (69) having a progressing cavity passage (71); and the non-rotating portion of the pump comprises a rotor (72) within the progressing cavity passage and having a progressing cavity exterior. 9. The assembly according to claim 1, wherein; the non-rotating portion of the pump comprises a stack of diffusers; 

 the rotating portion of the pump comprises an impeller rotatably mounted between each of the diffusers; each of the magnets is mounted to one of the impellers; the assembly further comprising: a support member mounted in the upstream end of the housing, the support member having a receptacle; an anchor secured to and protruding from an upstream end of the stack of diffusers, the anchor being received within the receptacle when the pump is in the landed position; mating torque surfaces between the anchor and the receptacle, preventing rotation of the anchor relative to the receptacle; and an intake passage (65) extending through the support member and the anchor to the diffusers. 10. The assembly according to claim 1, wherein; the rotating portion of the pump comprises a tube having a progressing cavity passage, the magnets (75) being mounted to the tube; the non-rotating portion of the pump comprises a rotor within the progressing cavity passage and having a progressing cavity exterior; a support member mounted in the upstream end of the housing, the support member having a receptacle; 

 an intake chamber (91) in the housing between the support member and the stator; a progressing cavity pump flex shaft (85) secured to and protruding from an upstream end of the rotor through the intake chamber; an anchor member (87) at an upstream end of the flex shaft, the anchor member being received within the receptacle while the pump is in the landed position; mating torque surfaces between the anchor member and the receptacle, preventing rotation of the anchor member relative to the receptacle; and an intake passage (89) extending through the anchor member to the intake chamber while the pump is in the landed position. 11. A method of pumping well fluid from a well, comprising: installing in the well a housing (33) having a longitudinal axis (19), the housing having a stator (37) with an axially extending stator cavity (39) and windings (127); placing in the stator cavity a first pump (41) having a non-rotating pump portion (43) and a rotating pump portion (45), the first pump having magnets (47) on the rotating pump portion; supplying power to the stator, creating an electromagnetic field that imparts rotation to the rotating pump portion in response to the electromagnetic field, causing well fluid to flow through the first pump and up the well; characterized by then lowering a running string into the well, engaging the first pump, and retrieving the first pump from the stator cavity. 12. The method according to claim 11, further comprising: after retrieving the first pump, attaching a running string to a second pump (67), then lowering the running string into the well and landing the second pump in the stator cavity. 13. The method according to claim 12, wherein one of the first and second pumps comprises a centrifugal pump (41) and the other of the first and second pumps comprises a progressing cavity pump (67). 14. The method according to claim 11, wherein: the first pump comprises a progressing cavity pump (67); the rotating portion of the progressing cavity pump comprises a tube (73) having a progressing cavity passage (71) ; and the non-rotating portion of the progressing cavity pump comprises a rotor (72) within the progressing cavity passage and having a progressing cavity exterior. 15. The method according to claim 11, wherein: the first pump comprises a centrifugal pump (41); and the second pump comprises a progressing cavity pump (67) with a stator (69) comprising the rotating pump portion and a rotor (72) comprising the non-rotating pump portion.
